<topic id="id_6" class="- topic/topic "><title class="- topic/title ">Configure data-driven commands and variables in the test case</title><body class="- topic/body "><p class="- topic/p ">Katalon Recorder also provides a simple user interface to configure data-driven commands and variables.</p><p class="- topic/p ">Follow these steps:</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li ">
                <p class="- topic/p ">Select the data file. Right-click on the data file and select <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Use this in a test case</b>.</p>
                <p class="- topic/p "> <image href="https://github.com/katalon-studio/docs-images/raw/master/katalon-recorder/docs/implement-ddt-in-a-test-case/KR-Use-this-in-a-test-case.png" scope="external" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Katalon Recorder use test data file</alt></image>
                </p>
            </li><li class="- topic/li ">
                <p class="- topic/p ">Select the test case. In the displayed menu, select the desired test case. Click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Next</b> to continue.</p>
                <p class="- topic/p ">Here we select the test case that we previously recorded.</p>
                <p class="- topic/p "> <image href="https://github.com/katalon-studio/docs-images/raw/master/katalon-recorder/docs/implement-ddt-in-a-test-case/KR-5.8.0-Select-test-case.png" scope="external" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Katalon Recorder select test case</alt></image>
                </p>
            </li><li class="- topic/li ">
                <p class="- topic/p ">Use the data from the data file. In the displayed test case, select the commands and specify the desired variables. Click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Add</b> when done.</p>
                <p class="- topic/p ">Katalon Recorder specifies a variable using the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">${&lt;variable_name&gt;}</codeph> syntax as a placeholder in the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Value</b> field. When executing the test case, Katalon Recorder expands the variable into its value.</p>
                <p class="- topic/p ">We want to use the comments from the CSV file, so we replace the current comment text with the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Comment</codeph> variable.</p>
                <p class="- topic/p "> <image href="https://github.com/katalon-studio/docs-images/raw/master/katalon-recorder/docs/implement-ddt-in-a-test-case/KR-5.8.0-Configure-variable.png" scope="external" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Katalon Recorder configure comment variable</alt></image>
                </p>
            </li><li class="- topic/li ">
                <p class="- topic/p ">Verify that the values in the test case are replaced with the correct variable.</p>
                <p class="- topic/p "> <image href="https://github.com/katalon-studio/docs-images/raw/master/katalon-recorder/docs/implement-ddt-in-a-test-case/KR-5.8.0-Test-case-configured-with-variable.png" scope="external" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Katalon Recorder configure comment variable</alt></image>
                </p>
            </li><li class="- topic/li ">
                <p class="- topic/p ">Play the test case and verify the results in the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Log</b> view. The log message should indicate that Katalon Recorder expands the specified variables into test data.</p>
                <p class="- topic/p "> <image href="https://github.com/katalon-studio/docs-images/raw/master/katalon-recorder/docs/implement-ddt-in-a-test-case/KR-5.8.0-Test-results.png" scope="external" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Katalon Recorder DDT results</alt></image>
                </p>
            </li></ol><p class="- topic/p "> <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">See also</b>: <ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li ">
                    <p class="- topic/p ">The Katalon Academy course: <xref format="html" href="https://academy.katalon.com/courses/katalon-recorder-data-driven-testing/" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">Data-Driven Testing with Katalon Recorder</xref>.</p>
                </li></ul></p></body></topic>